feat: demo kill-shot seed, copy/share buttons, stats tests, README

Addresses four follow-ups:

1. Auto-roast works out of the box. lib/sportsapi.ts ships a bundled SEED
   result (Brazil 2-1 Argentina, QF) merged into getAllResults() at lowest
   priority (seed < manual/tmp < live feed). So "Hold me to it" produces a
   real WRONG verdict for the demo even before any result is fed. Toggle off
   with DENDAM_SEED_RESULTS=off. (Inlined as a const, not a JSON file, because
   data/ is gitignored and would break the Vercel build.)

2. Copy/share buttons. components/ShareButton.tsx — Web Share API with a
   clipboard fallback. Wired into /share/[handle] (CTA row) and the dossier
   badge row (Copy link).

3. Tests. tests/stats.test.ts (statsForHandle tallies/accuracy/topLine
   priority) + two getAllResults seed tests in sportsapi.test.ts. 39 -> 44.

4. README. Documents the light UI, ?handle= deep-links, /share pages + OG
   cards, and the bundled seed; updated architecture tree and test count.

Verified: build green, 44/44 tests; live-local reconcile of the demo handle
yielded two WRONG verdicts and the /share card now shows 2 wrong calls, 0%
accuracy, and the roast quote.

